definition.value: An L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl-(1->4)-D-GlcpNS in which both anomeric centres have alpha configuration.
A disaccharide that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-L-fucopyranoside.
A glycosyl alditol resulting from the formal condensation of beta-D-galactopyranose with the hydroxy group at position 3 of galactitol.
A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose, 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose and N-acetyl-D-galactosaminitol residues joined in sequence by (1->3) glycosidic bonds.
A disaccharide that is D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 4 has been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-dexoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
A D-fucofuranose that has alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.
